Package: evfuse
Title: Spatial Data Fusion for Extreme Value Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Brian N.", "White", email = "bnw@unc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Brian", "Blanton", role = "aut"),
    person("Rick", "Luettich", role = "aut"),
    person("Richard L.", "Smith", role = "aut"))
Description: Two-stage frequentist framework for fusing sparse observations
    and dense simulations for spatial extreme value analysis. Fits generalized
    extreme value (GEV) distributions independently at each site, then models
    the site-level parameter estimates jointly via a linear model of
    coregionalization with a selection matrix that accommodates partial
    observations. Developed for U.S. coastal sea levels (White et al., 2025)
    but applicable to any setting where annual maxima from multiple spatial
    data sources can be fused.
